Release Notes
In summary, the key additions in the second version of the TRIN Trading Strategy include:

• A dynamic TRIN threshold based on moving averages and standard deviations, making the strategy more adaptive to market conditions.

• A volatility-based stop loss, improving risk management by setting stop loss levels that adjust with price volatility.

• New input parameters that provide greater customization for threshold calculations and stop loss levels, enhancing the strategy’s flexibility.

These features collectively improve the robustness of the strategy, allowing for more informed and adaptive trading decisions.
